<subSubSection id="B6DC9EABFF9EFFC4FF1C776ED9DFFA82" pageId="47" pageNumber="60" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="FE79CD20FF9EFFC4FF1C776ED978FCC2" blockId="47.[151,757,585,1281]" pageId="47" pageNumber="60">
<emphasis id="CCB21132FF9EFFC4FF1C776ED97EFDE2" bold="true" box="[151,262,585,609]" pageId="47" pageNumber="60">Comment</emphasis>
: The original description is based on a unique male from 
<collectingCountry id="86D18DB0FF9EFFC4FE92774ED91CFD02" box="[281,356,617,641]" name="Brunei" pageId="47" pageNumber="60">Brunei</collectingCountry>
. The specific epithet is evidently a misspelling: in the heading of the description 
<bibRefCitation id="9A57B0D1FF9EFFC4FD3577AED8A4FD42" author="PACE, R." pageId="47" pageNumber="60" pagination="743 - 769" refId="ref77939" refString="PACE, R. 2007: Le specie del genere Orphnebius MOTSCHULSCKY [sic], 1858, nel Borneo (Coleoptera, Staphylinidae). - Revue Suisse de Zoologie 114 (4): 743 - 769." type="journal article" year="2007">PACE (2007)</bibRefCitation>
writes “ 
<taxonomicName id="39C6B6A3FF9EFFC4FEB0778ED9E6FD42" box="[315,414,681,705]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Orphnebius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="47" pageNumber="60" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="kripticola">
<emphasis id="CCB21132FF9EFFC4FEB0778ED9E6FD42" box="[315,414,681,705]" italics="true" pageId="47" pageNumber="60">kripticola</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
”, whereas in other parts of the article (abstract, résumé, keys, figure caption) he uses the – etymologically correct – epithet “ 
<taxonomicName id="39C6B6A3FF9EFFC4FD8577CEDA0EFC82" authorityName="PACE" authorityYear="2007" box="[526,630,745,769]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Orphnebius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="47" pageNumber="60" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="krypticola">
<emphasis id="CCB21132FF9EFFC4FD8577CEDA0EFC82" box="[526,630,745,769]" italics="true" pageId="47" pageNumber="60">krypticola</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
” five times. 
<bibRefCitation id="9A57B0D1FF9EFFC4FF1C762DD9FFFCA2" author="HLAVAC, P. &amp; NEWTON, A. F. &amp; MARUYAMA, M." box="[151,391,777,805]" pageId="47" pageNumber="60" pagination="1 - 151" refId="ref77416" refString="HLAVAC, P.; NEWTON, A. F. &amp; MARUYAMA, M. 2011: World catalogue of the species of the tribe Lomechusini (Staphylinidae: Aleocharinae). - Zootaxa 3075: 1 - 151." type="journal article" year="2011">HLAVÁČ et al. (2011)</bibRefCitation>
list the species as 
<taxonomicName id="39C6B6A3FF9EFFC4FDF1762ED882FCC2" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Orphnebius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="47" pageNumber="60" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="kripticola">
<emphasis id="CCB21132FF9EFFC4FDF1762ED882FCC2" italics="true" pageId="47" pageNumber="60">Orphnebius kripticola</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="FE79CD20FF9EFFC4FF1C766ED934FB02" blockId="47.[151,757,585,1281]" pageId="47" pageNumber="60">
The fact that 
<bibRefCitation id="9A57B0D1FF9EFFC4FEBB766ED9CDFCE2" author="PACE, R." box="[304,437,841,865]" pageId="47" pageNumber="60" pagination="743 - 769" refId="ref77939" refString="PACE, R. 2007: Le specie del genere Orphnebius MOTSCHULSCKY [sic], 1858, nel Borneo (Coleoptera, Staphylinidae). - Revue Suisse de Zoologie 114 (4): 743 - 769." type="journal article" year="2007">PACE (2007)</bibRefCitation>
uses the epithet “ 
<taxonomicName id="39C6B6A3FF9EFFC4FD0A766EDA91FCE2" authorityName="PACE" authorityYear="2007" box="[641,745,841,865]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Orphnebius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="47" pageNumber="60" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="krypticola">
<emphasis id="CCB21132FF9EFFC4FD0A766EDA91FCE2" box="[641,745,841,865]" italics="true" pageId="47" pageNumber="60">krypticola</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
” five times, as opposed to one occurrence of “ 
<taxonomicName id="39C6B6A3FF9EFFC4FDE5764EDAA9FC02" box="[622,721,873,897]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Orphnebius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="47" pageNumber="60" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="kripticola">
<emphasis id="CCB21132FF9EFFC4FDE5764EDAA9FC02" box="[622,721,873,897]" italics="true" pageId="47" pageNumber="60">kripticola</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
”, is evidence that he meant to use the etymologically correct noun and that the spelling “ 
<taxonomicName id="39C6B6A3FF9EFFC4FE33768EDA63FC42" box="[440,539,937,961]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Orphnebius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="47" pageNumber="60" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="kripticola">
<emphasis id="CCB21132FF9EFFC4FE33768EDA63FC42" box="[440,539,937,961]" italics="true" pageId="47" pageNumber="60">kripticola</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
” represents an inadvertant error in the sense of Article 32.5.1 of the Code (
<bibRefCitation id="9A57B0D1FF9EFFC4FF1576CED958FB82" author="ICZN" box="[158,288,1001,1025]" pageId="47" pageNumber="60" refId="ref77457" refString="ICZN 1999: International Code of Zoological Nomenclature. Fourth Edition. - London: XXIX + 306 pp." type="book" year="1999">ICZN 1999</bibRefCitation>
). According to Article 24.2.3 of the Code, 
<bibRefCitation id="9A57B0D1FF9EFFC4FF1C712DD90FFBA2" author="HLAVAC, P. &amp; NEWTON, A. F. &amp; MARUYAMA, M." box="[151,375,1033,1061]" pageId="47" pageNumber="60" pagination="1 - 151" refId="ref77416" refString="HLAVAC, P.; NEWTON, A. F. &amp; MARUYAMA, M. 2011: World catalogue of the species of the tribe Lomechusini (Staphylinidae: Aleocharinae). - Zootaxa 3075: 1 - 151." type="journal article" year="2011">HLAVÁČ et al. (2011)</bibRefCitation>
cannot be regarded as First Revisers, since they do not cite both spellings together. Thus, the epithet “ 
<taxonomicName id="39C6B6A3FF9EFFC4FE96716ED9FDFBE2" authorityName="PACE" authorityYear="2007" box="[285,389,1097,1121]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Orphnebius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="47" pageNumber="60" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="krypticola">
<emphasis id="CCB21132FF9EFFC4FE96716ED9FDFBE2" box="[285,389,1097,1121]" italics="true" pageId="47" pageNumber="60">krypticola</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
” is here designated as the correct original spelling.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="FE79CD20FF9EFFC4FF1C71AED9DFFA82" blockId="47.[151,757,585,1281]" pageId="47" pageNumber="60">
Based on the shapes of tergite and sternite VIII, as well as on the male sexual characters (ventral process massive; paramerite slender and curved), 
<taxonomicName id="39C6B6A3FF9EFFC4FE7271EEDA06FB62" authorityName="PACE" authorityYear="2007" box="[505,638,1225,1249]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Orphnebius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="47" pageNumber="60" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="krypticola">
<emphasis id="CCB21132FF9EFFC4FE7271EEDA06FB62" box="[505,638,1225,1249]" italics="true" pageId="47" pageNumber="60">O. krypticola</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
belongs to the 
<taxonomicName id="39C6B6A3FF9EFFC4FF3471CED94FFA82" authorityName="Assing" authorityYear="2016" box="[191,311,1257,1281]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Orphnebius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="47" pageNumber="60" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="reductus">
<emphasis id="CCB21132FF9EFFC4FF3471CED94FFA82" box="[191,311,1257,1281]" italics="true" pageId="47" pageNumber="60">O. reductus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
subgroup.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
